The '''Klaer Lightende Spiegel der Verfkonst''' (literally: "clearly lighting mirror of the painting art") is a [[manuscript]] with over 700 pages<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.de/books?id=5W18DQAAQBAJ&pg=PA139|title=Red: The History of a Color|last=Pastoureau|first=Michel|date=2017-02-14|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=9780691172774|language=en}}</ref> of color swatches, produced in 1692<ref name=Tdc /> by a Dutch author from Delft known only as A. Boogert.<ref name=bulbib /> The book is arranged according to the Aristotelian system rather than the spectrum, which had recently been described by [[Isaac Newton|Newton]].<ref name=":0" /> Only one copy of the manual is known, and it is completely handwritten and hand-painted.<ref name=kwakkel /> It is kept in the [[Bibliothèque Méjanes]] in [[Aix-en-Provence]].<ref name=cardon /> The book has been digitised and made available on [[E-Corpus]].
